{{Quote|Phobium was mined by Emperor Palpatine on Gargon. And there's only one thing I know of that he ever used it for: to coat the power core of the Death Star.|Admiral Ackbar|<ref name="TGoDV">''[[The Glove of Darth Vader]]''</ref>}}
'''Phobium''' was an metal alloy<ref name="TCSWE">{{CSWECite|III|24|Phobium}}</ref> mined on the planets [[Gargon/Legends|Gargon]],<ref name="TGoDV" /> [[Dor]],<ref name="EatMS">{{GamerCite|9|Endor and the Moddell Sector}}</ref> and [[Bonadan/Legends|Bonadan]].<ref name="BoB">''[[Star Wars Missions 19: Bounty on Bonadan]]''</ref>

It was first discovered many millennia before the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]] for use in [[Power cell/Legends|power cells]]. [[Jedi Knight/Legends|Jedi Knights]] would sometimes use phobium power cells and [[Crude phobium emitter|emitters]] for their [[Lightsaber/Legends|lightsabers]].<ref name="KotOR2">''[[Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic II: The Sith Lords]]''</ref> During the [[Galactic War]], between [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]] and [[Sith Empire (Post–Great Hyperspace War)|Sith Empire]], phobium was used to build [[Armor/Legends|armors]] and weapons.<ref name="TOR">''[[Star Wars: The Old Republic]]''</ref>

During the early years of the Galactic Civil War, [[Galactic Emperor/Legends|Emperor]] [[Palpatine/Legends|Palpatine]] stationed work crews on Gargon to mine the element. The ore on Dor was processed and mixed with [[Doonium/Legends|doonium]] compounds, which in turn were used to coat the power core of the<ref name="TGoDV" /> two [[Death Star/Legends|Death Stars]].<ref name="TCSWE" />

